{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844871331,"sessionID":"ses_2876839cdffety9R5MKCENZfTw","part":{"id":"prt_d7897d0fc001Yt14P7BRDNxesb","messageID":"msg_d7897c722001XQwebymSBwqFB0","sessionID":"ses_2876839cdffety9R5MKCENZfTw","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_1be2677a800e46379aa2c1fd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure (all directories and key files)\n2. Any existing specs, designs, or documentation related to AR-017 PicoD JWT middleware\n3. Any existing code in pkg/picod directory\n4. Go module configuration (go.mod)\n5. Any existing middleware patterns or JWT-related code in the project\n6. Test patterns used in the project\n\nSearch for files matching patterns like:\n- **/* (top level directory structure)\n- **/picod/**\n- **/*.go\n- **/go.mod\n- **/*jwt*\n- **/*spec*\n- **/*design*\n- **/*AR-017*\n- **/*ST-4*\n- **/*ST-3*\n\nRead any relevant files you find. Return the complete project structure, any specs/designs for AR-017, existing pkg/picod code, go.mod contents, and any patterns I should follow.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_287681767ffe32tMp9y486eYnL (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is the complete analysis of the agentcube project.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Project Structure\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n├── .sdd_prompt.md                          # SDD prompt for AR-017 design generation\n├── go.mod                                  # Go module: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube (go 1.25.0)\n├── go.sum\n├── coverage.out\n├── project.md / proposal.md / design.md / delta-spec.md / test_spec.md   # Root-level docs\n│\n├── changes/                                # All AR (Architecture Requests) organized by number\n│   ├── AR-001/ through AR-016/             # Previous completed changes\n│   └── AR-017/                             # CURRENT: PicoD JWT Middleware\n│       ├── proposal.md\n│       ├── design.md\n│       ├── delta-spec.md\n│       └── tasks.md\n│\n├── cmd/\n│   └── picod/main.go                       # PicoD daemon entry point\n│\n├── pkg/\n│   ├── apis/runtime/v1alpha1/              # CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n│   ├── common/types/types.go               # Shared types\n│   ├── picod/                              # PicoD sandbox daemon (TARGET of AR-017)\n│   │   ├── auth.go / auth_test.go          # JWT AuthMiddleware (ALREADY IMPLEMENTED)\n│   │   ├── server.go / server_test.go      # Gin server with route registration\n│   │   ├── config.go / config_test.go      # CLI flag parsing\n│   │   ├── types.go                        # Constants + request/response types\n│   │   ├── execute.go / execute_test.go    # Command execution handler\n│   │   ├── files.go                        # Legacy file handlers (upload, list, download)\n│   │   ├── health_test.go                  # Health check tests\n│   │   ├── sanitize_test.go                # Path sanitization tests\n│   │   └── files/                          # New file manager subpackage\n│   │       ├── manager.go / manager_test.go\n│   │       ├── types.go\n│   │       ├── sanitize.go / sanitize_test.go\n│   │       ├── read.go / read_test.go\n│   │       ├── write.go / write_test.go\n│   │       ├── upload.go / download.go\n│   │       ├── list.go / stat.go / search.go\n│   │       ├── mkdir.go / move.go / delete.go / chmod.go\n│   ├── router/                             # Router service (JWT issuer + proxy)\n│   │   ├── jwt.go / jwt_test.go            # JWTManager (RS256 key gen, sign, verify)\n│   │   ├── middleware.go / middleware_test.go  # AuthMiddleware, logging, trace ID\n│   │   ├── server.go / server_test.go      # Router HTTP server\n│   │   ├── config.go / config_test.go      # Router config\n│   │   ├── router.go / backend.go / loadbalancer.go\n│   │   ├── proxy.go / informer.go / session_manager.go\n│   │   ├── health.go / errors.go\n│   ├── store/                              # Session store (Redis/Valkey)\n│   │   ├── store.go / codec.go / singleton.go\n│   │   ├── store_redis.go / store_redis_test.go\n│   │   └── store_valkey.go / store_valkey_test.go\n│   └── workloadmanager/                    # K8s workload management\n│       ├── handler/                        # Sandbox lifecycle handlers\n│       ├── reconciler/                     # Pod reconciliation logic\n│       └── response/                       # Response utilities\n│\n├── client-go/                              # Generated K8s client code\n│   ├── clientset/                          # Typed clientset for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter\n│   ├── informers/                          # Shared informer factory\n│   └── listers/                            # Lister implementations\n│\n├── ci-cd/ / deployment/ / integrations/    # Ops/infra feature specs\n├── sandbox-orchestration/ / session-routing/ / session-store/\n├── cli-toolkit/ / code-execution/ / python-sdk/ / idle-cleanup/\n│   └── (each has design.md + spec.md)\n│\n└── testing/\n    └── agentcube_tdd_manifest.md\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. AR-017 PicoD JWT Middleware -- Complete Specs/Designs\n\nAll four AR-017 documents exist at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/`:\n\n### proposal.md (269 lines)\n- **Purpose**: Add JWT auth middleware to PicoD so only Router-signed requests can access sandbox resources\n- **Scope**: AuthManager (RSA public key + RWMutex), AuthMiddleware (RS256 validation, Bearer token, 1-min leeway, MaxBytesReader), route integration (`/api` protected, `/health` public)\n- **Out of scope**: Router JWT signing (AR-011), K8s Secret management, RBAC, token refresh, mTLS\n- **Error format**: `{\"error\": \"...\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"...\"}`\n- **Dependencies**: `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` v5.2.1 (already in go.mod), gin, crypto/rsa, crypto/x509\n\n### design.md (462 lines)\n- **Architecture**: Full data flow diagram (Client -> Router -> PicoD)\n- **Data structures**: `AuthManager{publicKey *rsa.PublicKey, mutex sync.RWMutex}`\n- **Methods**: `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()`, `AuthMiddleware()`, `newAuthManager()`, `checkFatal()`\n- **Constants**: `PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`, `MaxBodySize = 32 << 20`\n- **Server changes**: Add `authManager *AuthManager` field to Server struct\n- **Route protection table**: `/health` = no auth; all `/api/*` = yes auth\n- **Middleware order**: `gin.Logger() -> gin.Recovery() -> AuthMiddleware() -> Handler`\n- **Error response matrix**: 5 scenarios with exact error/detail strings\n- **Test matrix**: 10 test functions covering all scenarios\n- **Implementation steps**: 4 phases, all marked `[x]` (completed)\n- **Deployment**: Key distribution flow from Router -> K8s Secret -> WorkloadManager -> PicoD env var\n\n### delta-spec.md (303 lines)\n- Gherkin-style Given/When/Then scenarios for every requirement\n- 9 requirements: AuthManager structure, AuthMiddleware validation, Route protection, Server initialization, Constants, Error consistency, Thread safety, Test coverage, Code quality gates\n\n### tasks.md (147 lines)\n- 7 task groups (T1-T7) with 40+ sub-tasks, all unchecked `[ ]`\n- Task dependency graph: T1 -> T2 -> T3 -> T4 (with T5, T6 parallel) -> T7\n- 10 acceptance criteria (AC1-AC10)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing pkg/picod Code\n\nThe picod package is **already fully implemented** for AR-017. Here is the current state:\n\n### `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/auth.go` (111 lines)\n- `AuthManager` struct with `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` and `mutex sync.RWMutex`\n- `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` -- reads `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`, PEM decodes, PKIX parses, RSA type checks\n- `AuthMiddleware()` -- extracts Bearer token, validates RS256 with exp/iat/leeway, wraps body with MaxBytesReader\n- `newAuthManager()` -- private constructor\n- `checkFatal()` -- klog.Fatalf wrapper\n\n### `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/server.go` (88 lines)\n- `Server` struct with `authManager *AuthManager` field\n- `NewServer()` creates AuthManager, loads public key, fatal-exits on failure\n- `registerRoutes()` applies `AuthMiddleware` to `/api` group; `/health` is unprotected\n- `Run()` starts HTTP server on configured port\n\n### `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/types.go` (51 lines)\n- Constants: `TimeoutExitCode = 124`, `MaxBodySize = 32 << 20`, `PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`, `maxFileMode = 0777`\n- Request/Response types: `ExecuteRequest`, `ExecuteResponse`, `FileInfo`, `UploadFileRequest`, `FileEntry`, `ListFilesResponse`\n\n### `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/config.go` (20 lines)\n- `Config{Port int, Workspace string}` with `ParseFlags()`\n\n### `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/execute.go` (108 lines)\n- `ExecuteHandler` -- command execution with timeout, working dir, env vars\n\n### `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files.go` (339 lines)\n- Legacy file handlers: `UploadFileHandler` (multipart + JSON base64), `ListFilesHandler`, `DownloadFileHandler`\n- `sanitizePath()` -- workspace jail enforcement\n\n### `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/` (sub-package)\n- New file manager with interface-based design: `FileManager` interface with 12 methods\n- Operations: ReadFile, WriteFile, StatFile, ListFiles, UploadFile, ChunkedUpload, DownloadFile, DeleteFile, MoveFile, MkDir, SearchFiles, Chmod\n- Each operation has its own file with request/response types\n\n### `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/picod/main.go` (15 lines)\n- Simple entry point: parse flags -> NewServer -> Run\n\n---\n\n## 4. Go Module Configuration\n\n**File**: `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/go.mod`\n\n```\nmodule github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\ngo 1.25.0\n```\n\nKey direct dependencies (relevant to AR-017):\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10.0 | HTTP middleware framework |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2.1 | JWT parsing and RS256 verification |\n| `github.com/stretchr/testify` | v1.11.1 | Testing (assert/require) |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.130.1 | Structured logging |\n| `k8s.io/api` | v0.34.1 | K8s API types |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | K8s client |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | K8s apimachinery |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing Middleware Patterns and JWT-Related Code\n\n### Router JWT Manager (`pkg/router/jwt.go`)\n- `JWTManager` struct: generates 2048-bit RSA key pairs, signs/verifies tokens\n- `GenerateToken(claims)` -- creates RS256 JWT with exp/iat/iss claims\n- `ParseAndValidateToken(tokenString)` -- validates with leeway, checks issuer\n- `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` -- stores/loads keys from K8s Secret `picod-router-identity`\n- Constants: `rsaKeySize = 2048`, `jwtExpiration = 5min`, `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n\n### Router AuthMiddleware (`pkg/router/middleware.go`)\n- `AuthMiddleware(jwtManager *JWTManager)` -- validates Bearer tokens via JWTManager\n- Error responses use string codes: `\"UNAUTHORIZED\"`, `\"TOKEN_EXPIRED\"`\n- Stores claims in Gin context: `c.Set(\"claims\", claims)`\n- Other middlewares: `ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware`, `RequestLoggerMiddleware`, `TraceIDMiddleware`\n\n### PicoD AuthMiddleware (`pkg/picod/auth.go`)\n- `AuthMiddleware()` method on `AuthManager` -- validates Bearer tokens using RSA public key\n- Error responses use numeric codes: `401`\n- Wraps body with `http.MaxBytesReader` after validation\n- Uses `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()`, `jwt.WithIssuedAt()`, `jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)`\n\n### Key architectural relationship:\n```\nRouter (JWTManager) --[signs RS256 token]--> PicoD (AuthManager) --[verifies with public key]\n```\nThe Router generates an RSA key pair, stores the public key in K8s Secret, WorkloadManager injects it into PicoD's `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var, and PicoD verifies incoming tokens.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test Patterns Used in the Project\n\n### Standard test structure (all picod tests follow this pattern):\n1. **Setup**: `gin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)`, set env vars with `os.Setenv`, defer `os.Unsetenv`\n2. **Server creation**: `NewServer(Config{Port: 0, Workspace: t.TempDir()})`\n3. **Request creation**: `httptest.NewRequest(method, path, body)`\n4. **Response recording**: `httptest.NewRecorder()`\n5. **Execution**: `server.engine.ServeHTTP(w, req)`\n6. **Assertions**: `assert.Equal(t, expectedCode, w.Code)`, `json.Unmarshal` for body checks\n\n### Test helper functions (in `auth_test.go`):\n```go\nfunc generateTestPrivateKey(t *testing.T) *rsa.PrivateKey    // 2048-bit RSA key\nfunc generateTestPublicKey(t *testing.T) string              // PEM-encoded public key\nfunc signTestToken(t *testing.T, key *rsa.PrivateKey, claims jwt.MapClaims) string\n```\n\n### Authed request helper (in `execute_test.go`):\n```go\nfunc authedRequest(t *testing.T, server *Server, method, path string, body []byte) *httptest.ResponseRecorder\n```\nThis helper generates a fresh key pair, sets the public key on the server's authManager, signs a token, and makes the request with the Bearer header.\n\n### Common test patterns:\n- **Table-driven tests**: Not heavily used; individual test functions per scenario\n- **Temp directories**: `t.TempDir()` for workspace isolation\n- **Environment variable cleanup**: `defer os.Unsetenv(PublicKeyEnvVar)`\n- **Test assertions**: `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert` and `require`\n- **Race detection**: Tests designed to pass with `go test -race`\n- **Gin test mode**: `gin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)` before creating engines\n\n### Test file inventory for picod:\n| File | Tests |\n|------|-------|\n| `auth_test.go` | 10 tests: LoadPublicKeyFromEnv (4 scenarios), AuthMiddleware (6 scenarios) |\n| `server_test.go` | 5 tests: field initialization, start time, health public, API requires auth, all routes registered |\n| `config_test.go` | 4 tests: flag defaults, custom values, empty workspace, relative workspace |\n| `execute_test.go` | 12 tests: valid execution, timeout, empty command, malformed JSON, exit codes, working dir, env vars, plus 3 constant tests |\n| `health_test.go` | 3 tests: response content, uptime increases, no auth required |\n| `sanitize_test.go` | 10 tests: traversal blocked, absolute path stripped, symlinks, empty workspace |\n| `files/manager_test.go`, `files/read_test.go`, `files/write_test.go`, `files/sanitize_test.go` | File manager sub-package tests |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_287681767ffe32tMp9y486eYnL","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775844714645,"end":1775844871328}}}}
