{"type":"text","timestamp":1775844916680,"sessionID":"ses_2876839cdffety9R5MKCENZfTw","part":{"id":"prt_d789ad084001BHLDEqd5hqcGi6","messageID":"msg_d789abdf0001Uod8li9AYbFSL3","sessionID":"ses_2876839cdffety9R5MKCENZfTw","type":"text","text":"Now I understand all 4 bugs. Let me fix them:\n\n1. **config.go**: Uses global `flag.Parse()` which panics on redefinition in tests — needs a new `FlagSet` per call\n2. **manager.go**: Doesn't validate empty workspace — test expects error for empty string\n3. **read.go**: `Seek(offset, io.SeekStart)` then reads — but test `\"hello world\"` offset 7 expects `\"world\"` (positions 7-11), getting `\"orld\"` means offset is 8 — off-by-one in the test expectations OR the implementation. Let me check: `\"hello world\"` = h(0)e(1)l(2)l(3)o(4) (5)w(6)o(7)r(8)l(9)d(10). Offset 7 = `'o'`, so `\"orld\"` is correct! The test expects `\"world\"` which is offset 6. The tests are wrong.\n4. **manager_test.go**: `assert.Equal(t, DefaultMaxChunkSize, fmImpl.maxChunkSize)` — `DefaultMaxChunkSize` is untyped const `32 << 20` = 33554432 which defaults to `int`, but `maxChunkSize` is `int64`.","time":{"start":1775844916678,"end":1775844916678}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844916801,"sessionID":"ses_2876839cdffety9R5MKCENZfTw","part":{"id":"prt_d789ae468001AtxPQ4OsOrsgzF","messageID":"msg_d789abdf0001Uod8li9AYbFSL3","sessionID":"ses_2876839cdffety9R5MKCENZfTw","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_91613b26de694bc7b43eec34","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/config.go","oldString":"package picod\n\nimport (\n\t\"flag\"\n)\n\ntype Config struct {\n\tPort      int    `json:\"port\"`\n\tWorkspace string `json:\"workspace\"`\n}\n\nfunc ParseFlags() Config {\n\tport := flag.Int(\"port\", 8080, \"Port for the PicoD server to listen on\")\n\tworkspace := flag.String(\"workspace\", \"\", \"Root directory for file operations (default: current working directory)\")\n\tflag.Parse()\n\treturn Config{\n\t\tPort:      *port,\n\t\tWorkspace: *workspace,\n\t}\n}","newString":"package picod\n\nimport (\n\t\"flag\"\n)\n\ntype Config struct {\n\tPort      int    `json:\"port\"`\n\tWorkspace string `json:\"workspace\"`\n}\n\nfunc ParseFlags() Config {\n\tfs := flag.NewFlagSet(\"picod\", flag.ContinueOnError)\n\tport := fs.Int(\"port\", 8080, \"Port for the PicoD server to listen on\")\n\tworkspace := fs.String(\"workspace\", \"\", \"Root directory for file operations (default: current working directory)\")\n\t_ = fs.Parse(os.Args[1:])\n\treturn Config{\n\t\tPort:      *port,\n\t\tWorkspace: *workspace,\n\t}\n}"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in this file, please fix:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/config.go\">\nERROR [16:15] undefined: os\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/server.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/