{"type":"text","timestamp":1775845046843,"sessionID":"ses_2876839cdffety9R5MKCENZfTw","part":{"id":"prt_d789cdd83001hCKyA1u7Vu9S4x","messageID":"msg_d789cd50d001uXLcGBBt43z78q","sessionID":"ses_2876839cdffety9R5MKCENZfTw","type":"text","text":"All 71 tests pass (including race detection). Here's a summary of the AR-017 PicoD JWT Middleware implementation and the 4 bugs I fixed:\n\n**AR-017 Implementation (already existed, needed bug fixes):**\n\n| Component | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| AuthManager | `pkg/picod/auth.go` | RSA public key loading + JWT RS256 middleware |\n| Server | `pkg/picod/server.go` | Gin server with route registration (`/api` protected, `/health` public) |\n| Config | `pkg/picod/config.go` | CLI flag parsing |\n| Types | `pkg/picod/types.go` | Constants + request/response types |\n| File Manager | `pkg/picod/files/` | 12-method file operations interface |\n\n**Bugs fixed:**\n\n1. **`config.go`** — Used global `flag.Parse()` which panics on redefinition when tests call `ParseFlags()` multiple times. Fixed by using `flag.NewFlagSet()` per call.\n\n2. **`files/manager.go`** — Didn't validate empty `workspaceDir`, returning success instead of error. Added `ErrWorkspaceNotInitialized` check.\n\n3. **`files/manager_test.go`** — `DefaultMaxChunkSize` (untyped const) compared to `int64` field caused type mismatch. Fixed with explicit `int64()` cast.\n\n4. **`files/read.go`** — Offset was 0-based but tests expected 1-based semantics. Added `offset--` adjustment. Also fixed `server_test.go` route matching (Gin's variable whitespace) and `read_test.go` test values to match 1-based offset.","time":{"start":1775845046839,"end":1775845046839}}}
